      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION CONSISTS OF ONE CLASS OF MEMBERS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>MEMBERS ARE ELECTED AS A RESULT OF FINDING OTHER PUBLICLY SUPPORTED HOSPITALS OR PUBLIC ENTITIES DOMICILED IN THE STATE OF TEXAS WHO DESIRE TO AFFILIATE WITH EACH OTHER IN ORDER TO IMPROVE HEALTH CARE DELIVERY IN THEIR RESPECTIVE COMMUNITIES.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE GOVERNING BODY CONSISTS ENTIRELY OF DIRECTORS/MEMBERS AND AS SUCH ALL DECISIONS OF THE GOVERNING BODY ARE THEREBY CONTEMPORANEOUSLY APPROVED BY THE MEMBERS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE GOVERNING BODY REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AT THE MEETING FOLLOWING THE COMPLETION OF THE RETURN.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES EACH DIRECTOR, PRINCIPAL OFFICER AND MEMBER TO ANNUALLY SIGN A STATEMENT WHICH AFFIRMS SUCH PERSON A) HAS RECEIVED A COPY OF THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, B) HAS READ AND UNDERSTANDS THE POLICY, C) HAS AGREED TO COMPLY WITH THE POLICY, AND D) UNDERSTANDS THE ORGANIZATION IS CHARITABLE AND IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN ITS FEDERAL TAX EXEMPTION IT MUST ENGAGE PRIMARILY IN ACTIVITIES WHICH ACCOMPLISH ONE OR MORE OF ITS TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSES. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION CONDUCTS PERIODIC REVIEWS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>EXCEPT AS PROVIDED FOR IN ITS FORM 1023 AND FORM 990S, THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT MAKE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY NOR FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
